# Workflow Session Rules - DigitalStudioz

## Start Project (cold boot)

When user says **Start Project**, **Begin Project**, or **Cold Start**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Start-Project.md`](../prompts/Start-Project.md)
- Run **`npm run session:start -- -Full`** from the DigitalStudioz profile root (`D:\\Hermes\\projects\\DigitalStudioz`)
- Read `TRUTH.md`, `.cursor/docs/START-HERE.md`, `.cursor/docs/ReCall.md`
- Do **not** auto-start long-running dev servers unless the operator explicitly asks

## Open Project (resume workspace)

When user says **Open Project** or **Resume Session**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Open-Project.md`](../prompts/Open-Project.md)
- Run **`npm run session:open`** (light probes — does **not** restart LiteLLM/ngrok if warm)
- Read `TRUTH.md`, `.cursor/docs/START-HERE.md`, `.cursor/docs/ReCall.md`
- Do **not** run `draven:speak` or `session:start -- -Full` unless stack is down and operator wants cold boot

## Close Project (switch workspace — keep fleet)

When user says **Close Project**, **Close Session**, or **Switch Project**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Close-Project.md`](../prompts/Close-Project.md)
- Update `.cursor/docs/ReCall.md` and `.cursor/docs/project-log.md`
- Run **`npm run session:handoff`** (vault note only — **no** `session:stop`)
- Use **AskQuestion** for git commit/push — never auto-commit
- Do **not** run `draven:speak` or `-StopDeepSeek`

## End Project (day-end)

When user says **End Project**, **End Session**, **Session Closeout**, or **Done for today**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/End-Project.md`](../prompts/End-Project.md)
- Update `.cursor/docs/ReCall.md` and `.cursor/docs/project-log.md`
- Use **AskQuestion** for git, then **AskQuestion** for **Stop LiteLLM + ngrok** (recommend stop)
- Run **`npm run session:stop`** (add **`-- -StopDeepSeek`** when operator confirms stop)

## Update Docs

When user says **update docs** or **update docs and mem0**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Update-Docs.md`](../prompts/Update-Docs.md)
- Run **`npm run docs:sync`**
- Run **`npm run version:sync`** when version changed
- Align version across `TRUTH.md`, `package.json`, `MASTER-COMMANDS.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`

## Release Version

When user says **release version**, **publish release**, or after a version bump on a milestone branch:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Release-Version.md`](../prompts/Release-Version.md)
- Run **`npm run version:sync`** then **`npm run release`**

## Branch Cut

When user says **branch cut**, **cut DigitalStudioz-Project-vN**, **cut new development branch**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Branch-Cut.md`](../prompts/Branch-Cut.md)
- Full ritual: backup -> freeze previous branch @ SHA -> create `DigitalStudioz-Project-v{N}` -> bump **`N.0.0`** -> update Restore-Points -> **`npm run release`**
- Do **not** stop at `git checkout -b` alone
- Leave **`main`** untouched unless the operator explicitly requests a merge

## Backup

When user says **backup profile** or **backup**:

- Run **`npm run backup:quick`** from profile root (non-interactive)

## Review Tool

When user pastes a **repo/product URL** or says **review tool**, **evaluate tool**, **add to watchlist**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Review-Tool.md`](../prompts/Review-Tool.md)
- Update shared canonical docs: `_core-scripts/shared-profile-content/docs/TOOLS-*.md`
- Run **`npm run tools:status`** after install to verify config queue

## Build Showcase Demo

When user says **Build Showcase Demo**, **Fire Showcase**, **Hermes Motion Lab**, **build motion lab**, or **ultimate demo site**:

- Execute [`.cursor/prompts/Build-Showcase-Demo.md`](../prompts/Build-Showcase-Demo.md)
- Read **`.cursor/docs/HERMES-SHOWCASE-SPEC.md`** — living spec + add queue
- Default target: **JonBeatz.dev** route `/showcase`

When user sends a **design reference URL** (no build yet):

- Append row to **DESIGN-REFERENCES.md** add queue **and** **HERMES-SHOWCASE-SPEC.md** add queue
